-- MOVES-Gall promotes Chris Wong to partner, hires senior associate
-- 
-- Mon Aug 18, 2014 03:39AM EDT
-- None



Aug 18 (Reuters) - Hong-Kong based law firm Gall promoted corporate and commercial disputes lawyer Chris Wong to a partner and hired Brooke Holden, a senior associate, from Pinsent Masons.

Wong, who is leading Gall's China practice, acts for a broad range of clients in corporate and commercial dispute work, with particular emphasis on complex multi-jurisdictional disputes, fraud and asset recovery. He joined the firm in October 2010. Holden, a senior disputes lawyer, advises in relation to domestic and international arbitration and other forms of dispute resolution, both in Hong Kong and abroad.